      • getNormalized

        public double getNormalized(T key)
        Given a key, returns the mean of the values provided for that key so far, normalized by the total number of entries (e.g., the number of addAll() calls). If addAll() was called and provided no value for the requested key, that is considered as providing the value "0", and so does reduce the mean.
        Specified by:

      • getItemCount

        public int getItemCount()
        Description copied from interface: WeightedSet
        Returns the number of items represented by this WeightedSet. This may differ both from the number of keys and from the sum of the values. When WeightedSets are aggregated via addAll, their item counts are added together.
        Specified by:
